Senior Data Scientist		KSM Consulting		Indianapolis, Indiana Area		<div class="rich-text" itemprop="description"><p><strong>Summary of Responsibilities:</strong><br /> Apply advanced mathematics and predictive analytics to solve some of our client's most challenging problems.  Work with a team to implement practical solutions that turn our findings into real results. </p><p></p><p><strong>Essential Functions:</strong> </p><ul><li>Apply and develop machine learning and other advanced analytics algorithms </li><li>Collaborate with software developers to plan and construct the architecture of model deployment </li><li>Maintain a working knowledge of data mining and visualization best practices </li><li>Architect backend development of advanced analytics and software solutions </li><li>Work closely with the data analytics practice director and other practice directors, solution architects, product manager, and project managers on requirements, solution architecture, and development execution. </li><li>Involvement in client-facing project activities such as requirements gathering, solution reviews, and explaining technical complexities and business benefits in layperson terms. </li><li>Helping define the data analytics solution delivery methodology. </li><li>R&amp;D and long-term positioning of the data analytics practice around current and emerging technologies.</li></ul></div><div class="rich-text" itemprop="description"><p>KSM Consulting is an Indianapolis-based business and technology consulting firm serving the public sector and private organizations across the United States. We help organizations assess, align, and optimize technology, data, personnel, and processes to fulfill their missions more effectively. </p><p></p><p>KSMC consultants love strengthening what they’re good at, and are constantly in search of ways to help others become stronger. What drives us as individuals is an abiding desire to master our craft. From there, our greatest satisfaction comes as we’re able to translate our abilities into value that makes a significant difference to our clients. </p><p></p><p>Over 70 employees and rapidly growing, KSM Consulting is part of the employee-owned Katz, Sapper &amp; Miller Network headquartered in Indianapolis, Indiana.</p></div>